{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"e51cc66c-41fb-4dbd-870f-f8c45bee0004","content":"PID 12345 doesn't exist on this machine, so I can't inspect it directly. Here's how to do both steps yourself:\n\n---\n\n### 1. Determine the runtime\n\n**Quick check — look for CoreCLR libraries in the process:**\n\n```bash\n# If this returns matches, it's CoreCLR\ncat /proc/12345/maps | grep -i 'libcoreclr\\|libclrjit'\n\n# Also check the binary itself — NativeAOT produces a fully static/self-contained ELF\nfile /proc/12345/exe\n```\n\n| Signal | CoreCLR | NativeAOT |\n|---|---|---|\n| `libcoreclr.so` loaded | ✅ | ❌ |\n| `libclrjit.so` loaded | ✅ | ❌ |\n| `file` shows dynamically linked to many .NET libs | ✅ | ❌ |\n| Binary is large, self-contained, no `.dll` files beside it | ❌ | ✅ |\n\n---\n\n### 2. Configure crash dumps\n\n#### **If CoreCLR:**\n\nSet environment variables for the process (e.g. in a systemd unit or wrapper script):\n\n```bash\nexport DOTNET_DbgEnableMiniDump=1          # Enable automatic dumps\nexport DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpType=4            # 4 = Full dump (1=Mini, 2=Heap, 3=Triage)\nexport DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpName=/tmp/coredump.%p.%t   # %p=PID, %t=timestamp\n```\n\nOr configure the Linux kernel core pattern globally:\n\n```bash\necho '/tmp/core.%e.%p.%t' | sudo tee /proc/sys/kernel/core_pattern\nulimit -c unlimited\n```\n\n#### **If NativeAOT:**\n\nNativeAOT apps don't have the `DOTNET_DbgEnableMiniDump` machinery. Use the **standard Linux kernel core dump** mechanism:\n\n```bash\n# Set core dump path\necho '/tmp/core.%e.%p.%t' | sudo tee /proc/sys/kernel/core_pattern\n\n# Remove size limit\nulimit -c unlimited\n\n# For systemd-managed services, also set in the unit file:\n#   [Service]\n#   LimitCORE=infinity\n```\n\nTo analyze NativeAOT dumps, use **GDB** or **LLDB** (not `dotnet-dump`), since there's no CoreCLR runtime to introspect.\n\n---\n\n**TL;DR:** Check `/proc/<pid>/maps` for `libcoreclr`. If present → use `DOTNET_DbgEnableMiniDump`. If not (NativeAOT) → use the kernel `core_pattern` + `ulimit -c unlimited`.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"b5058b01-4ba9-481e-8d54-fdc3d739bf50","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The process doesn't exist on this machine (PID 12345 is fictional). Let me provide the user with guidance on how to determine the runtime and configure dumps accordingly.","outputTokens":749,"requestId":"6817:1E23:5A0A81:6841D8:69FD42E1"},"id":"b48d5fb2-9331-4a9d-8b2e-44478f11c4c6","timestamp":"2026-05-08T01:57:08.296Z","parentId":"bda79fa7-1dd2-4cb6-a650-77abf5a5105b"}
